news.title: Central government releases Rs 187 crore for Kanpur development body's projects
news.para: The state government had forwarded the proposal for the funds allocation which could be spent on various development programmes. KDA vice-chairman Vishak G Iyer has taken steps to execute the New Kanpur City and Bingawan residential schemes.

news.title: Government seeks information on Gurugram civic body's colony takeover for audit
news.para: The queries, sent to the senior town planner (STP), mainly include the status of DPRs for deficient infrastructure amounting to Rs 92 crore in the colony takeover and what action was taken if the builders of seven colonies didn’t seek completion certificates.

news.title: Over 6,700 properties sealed for tax default in Ahmedabad
news.para: The most sealed properties, 3,111, are in areas in the civic body’s East Zone. The AMC also demolished seven illegal structures in the Lambha area.

news.title: Architects could soon approve building plans: Karnataka deputy CM
news.para: Shivakumar said, “People have to run from pillar to post in BBMP to obtain building approvals. We will soon issue a government order enabling authorised architects to self-declare building plan without having the need to get it approved from the Palike.”

news.title: Halan family buys apartments in South Mumbai's Mahalaxmi for Rs 104 crore
news.para: Several members of the family have purchased these apartments on the 23rd, 24th, 25th, and 26th floor of luxury project Raheja Modern Vivarea on Jacob Circle from the developer K Raheja Corp.

news.title: PM hands over 15,000 homes under largest affordable housing project
news.para: The project, spanning 350 acres, is divided into two phases and will construct a total of 30,000 flats across 833 buildings. Each dwelling unit costs Rs 6.10 lakh, including infrastructure priced at Rs 5,00,000.

news.title: Noida authority's own panel to inspect old buildings before safety audit
news.para: The committee will step in after the builder or Apartment Owners Association (AOA) submit a request to get the flats audited.

news.title: Gurugram: Another Chintel Paradiso tower declared 'unsafe,' evacuation ordered
news.para: ​Six floors of Tower D of Chintels Paradiso society had collapsed partially on February 10, 2022 leading to the death of two female residents. Since then, the building site has been a matter of dispute between the builder and residents.

news.title: HC asks Supertech's chairman to respond to ED's plea challenging interim bail
news.para: The high court noted that Arora, who was granted interim bail by a trial court here on Tuesday, has already been released from jail and listed the matter for further hearing on February 9.

news.title: Anant Raj raises Rs 500 crore via QIP
news.para: Company will use part of the funds raised to bring down the debt and for working capital requirements, according to a source.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit grows 67% to Rs 1,774.7 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: UltraTech Cement's revenue from operations rose 7.85 per cent to Rs 16,739.97 crore during the period. It was Rs 15,520.93 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: Chennai: ED raids Ocean Lifespaces India, promoters in money laundering case
news.para: ​The probe by the central agency was initiated after taking cognisance of an FIR filed by the central crime branch (CCB) of Greater Chennai Police against Ocean Lifespaces India Private Limited, its MD and CEO S K Peter, some directors and others.

news.title: MMRDA signs MOU with government of Netherlands for sustainable urban development
news.para: A Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) was signed between MMRDA with the Netherland’s Ministry of Infrastructure and Water Management to enforce sustainable urban development in the MMR at the World Economic Forum, Davos 2024.

news.title: Pune: Centre's nod to Katraj Metro plan in a month
news.para: The 5.5km Ruby Hall Clinic to Ramwadi Metro section is slated for final inspection and approval by the Commissioner of Metro Railway Safety (CMRS) next week, while Swargate-Katraj underground stretch is likely to receive the Centre’s approval in a month.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Housing project told to fix solar power panels on 50% roof area
news.para: The project has been designed with a total built-up area of 32,034.68 m2, a total land/plot area of 0.9849ha, and a proposed FAR (floor area ratio) of 20,690.88sq.m.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body cracks down on illegal buildings
news.para: The MC officials took action against three commercial illegal buildings which were under construction in Model town market, on Model Town-Jawaddi road (near Mint Gumri chowk) and in Model Town extension area.

news.title: Property rates in top 13 cities rise 19 per cent in Q3: Magicbricks Propindex Report
news.para: The affordable housing market saw strong growth in Ahmedabad (62%) and Kolkata (48%) while luxury properties were most searched in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (90%), New Delhi (58%), and Gurugram (48%).

news.title: Deadline looms, just 78,000 property tags issued in Delhi
news.para: MCD has around 14 lakh taxpayers and around 13 lakh properties have been issued the unique property identification code (UPIC) number.

news.title: Mumbai: 24-acre Bandra sprawl put up for development, builder must be worth Rs 15,000 crore
news.para: “The biggest builders will find themselves ineligible to bid. It looks like the tender has been tailor-made for a select few,’’ said a developer, whose representative attended the pre-bid meeting.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audit of 22 highrises held up as builders yet to pay fee
news.para: A total of 23 highrise societies were selected for the second phase of structural audit, but only one has paid the fee so far.
